framework_component_specs.ArticleCard:
# ArticleCard — React Router (`.tsx`)

## Purpose
Article preview card with a full-bleed image, gradient overlay, date, author avatar, and title. Used in React Router article listings and related-article route sections.

## Props

### Required
| Prop | Type | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `href` | `string` | Link target for the full article. Use a React Router route path. |
| `title` | `string` | Article title. |
| `image` | `string` | Image URL rendered full-bleed inside the card. |

### Optional
| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `description` | `string` | - | Short description/excerpt. |
| `imageAlt` | `string` | `title` | Alt text for image. |
| `date` | `string` | - | Formatted date string. |
| `datetime` | `string` | - | ISO date for `<time>`. |
| `author` | `Author` | - | Author object with name and avatar. |
| `ctaText` | `string` | `'Read more'` | Call-to-action text. |
| `className` | `string` | - | Additional CSS classes. |
| `variant` | `'default' \| 'compact'` | `'default'` | Card size variant. |

```ts
type Author = {
    name: string;
    avatar: string;
};
```

## Semantic Hints
`card`, `article-card`, `preview`, `teaser`, `post-card`, `blog-card`, `article-preview`, `content-card`

## When to Use
Use in React Router route modules for article index pages, category pages, and related-article sections. Do not typically use inside long-form article body content.

## Structure
```txt
<Link>
  └── <article>
      ├── Image
      ├── Gradient Overlay
      └── Bottom Content
          ├── Date
          ├── Title
          ├── Description
          ├── Author
          └── CTA Text
```

## Styling Guidelines
- Use Tailwind CSS utilities.
- Keep a consistent aspect ratio: `aspect-video` by default, shorter for compact cards.
- Use a dark gradient overlay for text contrast.
- Title should be bold and prominent.
- Hover state should slightly scale the image and increase shadow.
- Compact variant should reduce padding and typography size.

## Accessibility
- The entire card is a single React Router `<Link>`.
- Image must have meaningful `alt` text.
- Date uses `<time dateTime={datetime}>` when provided.
- Ensure sufficient contrast for overlaid text.
- Author avatar should be decorative if the author name is already rendered.

## Complete React Router Example

`app/routes/articles.tsx`

```tsx
